   <title>
      <keyword>link</keyword>
   </title>
   <shortdesc>The &lt;<keyword>link</keyword>&gt; element defines a relationship
to another topic. Links represent the types and roles of topics
in a web of information, and therefore represent navigational links within
that web. The parent structures of link allow authors to define named groups
and even sort orders that can be applied to sets of links.  </shortdesc>
